verses.text: And the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* spake unto Moses and to Aaron , saying unto them,
Speak unto the children of Israel , saying , These \add are\add* the beasts which ye shall eat among all the beasts that \add are\add* on the earth.
Whatsoever parteth the hoof , and is clovenfooted , \add and\add* cheweth the cud , among the beasts , that shall ye eat.

Nevertheless these shall ye not eat of them that chew the cud , or of them that divide the hoof : \add as\add* the camel , because he cheweth the cud , but divideth not the hoof ; he \add is\add* unclean unto you.
And the coney , because he cheweth the cud , but divideth not the hoof ; he \add is\add* unclean unto you.
And the hare , because he cheweth the cud , but divideth not the hoof ; he \add is\add* unclean unto you.
And the swine , though he divide the hoof , and be clovenfooted , yet he cheweth not the cud ; he \add is\add* unclean to you.
Of their flesh shall ye not eat , and their carcase shall ye not touch ; they \add are\add* unclean to you. \p
¶ These shall ye eat of all that \add are\add* in the waters : whatsoever hath fins and scales in the waters , in the seas , and in the rivers , them shall ye eat.

And all that have not fins and scales in the seas , and in the rivers , of all that move in the waters , and of any living thing which \add is\add* in the waters , they \add shall be\add* an abomination unto you:
They shall be even an abomination unto you; ye shall not eat of their flesh , but ye shall have their carcases in abomination.
Whatsoever hath no fins nor scales in the waters , that \add shall be\add* an abomination unto you. \p
¶ And these \add are they which\add* ye shall have in abomination among the fowls ; they shall not be eaten , they \add are\add* an abomination : the eagle , and the ossifrage , and the ospray ,
And the vulture , and the kite after his kind ;
Every raven after his kind ;
And the owl , and the night hawk , and the cuckow , and the hawk after his kind ,
And the little owl , and the cormorant , and the great owl ,
And the swan , and the pelican , and the gier eagle ,
And the stork , the heron after her kind , and the lapwing , and the bat. \p
All fowls that creep , going upon \add all\add* four , \add shall be\add* an abomination unto you.
Yet these may ye eat of every flying creeping thing that goeth upon \add all\add* four , which have legs above their feet , to leap withal upon the earth ;
\add Even\add* these of them ye may eat ; the locust after his kind , and the bald locust after his kind , and the beetle after his kind , and the grasshopper after his kind.
But all \add other\add* flying creeping things , which have four feet , \add shall be\add* an abomination unto you.
And for these ye shall be unclean : whosoever toucheth the carcase of them shall be unclean until the even.
And whosoever beareth \add ought\add* of the carcase of them shall wash his clothes , and be unclean until the even.

\add The carcases\add* of every beast which divideth the hoof , and \add is\add* not clovenfooted , nor cheweth the cud , \add are\add* unclean unto you: every one that toucheth them shall be unclean.
And whatsoever goeth upon his paws , among all manner of beasts that go on \add all\add* four , those \add are\add* unclean unto you: whoso toucheth their carcase shall be unclean until the even.
And he that beareth the carcase of them shall wash his clothes , and be unclean until the even : they \add are\add* unclean unto you. \p
¶ These also \add shall be\add* unclean unto you among the creeping things that creep upon the earth ; the weasel , and the mouse , and the tortoise after his kind ,
And the ferret , and the chameleon , and the lizard , and the snail , and the mole.
These \add are\add* unclean to you among all that creep : whosoever doth touch them, when they be dead , shall be unclean until the even.

And upon whatsoever \add any\add* of them, when they are dead , doth fall , it shall be unclean ; whether \add it be\add* any vessel of wood , or raiment , or skin , or sack , whatsoever vessel \add it be\add*, wherein \add any\add* work is done , it must be put into water , and it shall be unclean until the even ; so it shall be cleansed.
And every earthen vessel , whereinto \add any\add* of them falleth , whatsoever \add is\add* in it shall be unclean ; and ye shall break it.
Of all meat which may be eaten , \add that\add* on which \add such\add* water cometh shall be unclean : and all drink that may be drunk in every \add such\add* vessel shall be unclean.

And every \add thing\add* whereupon \add any part\add* of their carcase falleth shall be unclean ; \add whether it be\add* oven , or ranges for pots, they shall be broken down : \add for\add* they \add are\add* unclean , and shall be unclean unto you.

Nevertheless a fountain or pit , \add wherein there is\add* plenty of water , shall be clean : but that which toucheth their carcase shall be unclean.\f + \fr 11.36 \ft wherein…: Heb. a gathering together of waters\f*
And if \add any part\add* of their carcase fall upon any sowing seed which is to be sown , it \add shall be\add* clean.
But if \add any\add* water be put upon the seed , and \add any part\add* of their carcase fall thereon, it \add shall be\add* unclean unto you.
And if any beast , of which ye may eat , die ; he that toucheth the carcase thereof shall be unclean until the even.
And he that eateth of the carcase of it shall wash his clothes , and be unclean until the even : he also that beareth the carcase of it shall wash his clothes , and be unclean until the even.
And every creeping thing that creepeth upon the earth \add shall be\add* an abomination ; it shall not be eaten.

Whatsoever goeth upon the belly , and whatsoever goeth upon \add all\add* four , or whatsoever hath more feet among all creeping things that creep upon the earth , them ye shall not eat ; for they \add are\add* an abomination.\f + \fr 11.42 \ft hath…: Heb. doth multiply feet\f* \p

Ye shall not make yourselves abominable with any creeping thing that creepeth , neither shall ye make yourselves unclean with them, that ye should be defiled thereby.\f + \fr 11.43 \ft yourselves abominable: Heb. your souls, etc\f*

For I \add am\add* the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* your God : ye shall therefore sanctify yourselves , and ye shall be holy ; for I \add am\add* holy : neither shall ye defile yourselves with any manner of creeping thing that creepeth upon the earth.
For I \add am\add* the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* that bringeth you up out of the land of Egypt , to be your God : ye shall therefore be holy , for I \add am\add* holy.
This \add is\add* the law of the beasts , and of the fowl , and of every living creature that moveth in the waters , and of every creature that creepeth upon the earth :
To make a difference between the unclean and the clean , and between the beast that may be eaten and the beast that may not be eaten.
